column5: Cant believe it! Ended the year by skunking! Got out for 2 hours on the 30th and 1 hour on 31st.  fishing was slow the first day, but was not expecting the skunkypoo to raise its ugly head the second day. Oh well thats fishing.  Kinda should have known it was gonna happen as everything was going wrong yesterday, snowblower broke, broke an expensive tie down, my buddy showed up with his plow just as i finished snowblowing in 35kmh winds after spending 2 hours fixing ignition on snowblower....then a skunk?...should have known ...lol  still fishing deep,jigs and minnows, still getting walleye suspended at 20'FOW over 50'FOW,just nothing on the second day. A few fish did show on screen, but did not matter what i tried...they weren't interested.  Trout fishing tomorrow   Here's the vid for the 30th Dec with my buddy in my flip-up. Darn nice to have the heater...it was freeeeeezing that day.   <object width="640" height="385"><param name="movie" value="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=T-4eeTh1X-E?fs=1&hl=en_US"></param><param'>http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=T-4eeTh1X-E?fs=1&hl=en_US"></param><param name="allowFullScreen" value="true"></param><param name="allowscriptaccess" value="always"></param><embed src="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=T-4eeTh1X-E?fs=1&hl=en_US" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" allowscriptaccess="always" allowfullscreen="true" width="640" height="385"></embed></object>

Happy New Year to you and yours, Simon. A skunking or two at the very end of the year is a good thing. Get them all out of the way to start the new year off on the right foot.....ok ok, 30.48 centimetres.......  Thanks for the report.

I know the feeling of skunking too well Simon    I got out yesterday and the targeted species did not want to come out and play  Daughter decided to sleep in so I ventured out solo     I did however manage to land a short fat perch on a white jig dressed with a teaser type body tipped with a 1" Gulp black shad  I made a short video of it Enjoy!!!
